{% render 'proof-checkout-url', section: section %}
<section class="faq-section" id="faq" style="padding:120px 40px;" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
  <div class="section-inner" style="max-width:820px;margin:0 auto;">
    <span class="section-label reveal">Quick answers</span>
    <h2 class="section-h2 reveal reveal-delay-1" id="speakable-what-is">Everything you need to know.</h2>

    <div class="faq-list reveal reveal-delay-2">

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-what-is-proof">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What is PROOF Display?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>PROOF Display is a <strong>$499 countertop hardware device</strong> for cafés, salons, and boutiques. It shows your live Google rating, Instagram follower count, POS orders, and daily promotions on a 10.1-inch screen. Customers tap the NFC base with their phone — the Google review form opens in under 8 seconds. The Social Proof tier (Google rating + Instagram) is <strong>free forever</strong> after the one-time hardware purchase.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-how-it-works">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How does PROOF generate reviews automatically?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>PROOF displays your live Google rating on a glowing 10-inch screen at your counter. When a satisfied customer sees it, they tap the NFC base with their phone — the Google review form opens instantly. No searching, no QR scanning, no typing a URL. The review happens <strong>in the moment of satisfaction</strong>, not an hour later at home. Portland pilot merchants averaged <strong>2.3× more reviews per month</strong> after installing PROOF.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-nfc-vs-qr">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Do NFC taps work better than QR codes for reviews?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>Yes. NFC taps convert to completed reviews at approximately <strong>7× the rate of QR codes</strong>. The difference is timing and friction. QR codes require the customer to open their camera, scan, wait for the page to load, navigate to the review form, and remember to do all of this — usually at home, after the moment of satisfaction has passed. NFC happens in the moment: one tap, form opens, review written. <em>(Methodology: NFC group — 61 taps, 43 reviews completed over 60 days; QR receipt comparison — same 10 merchants, same period, 187 receipts distributed, 27 reviews completed.)</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-review-count">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How many Google reviews do I need to rank locally?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>Businesses with <strong>50+ Google reviews and a rating above 4.3★</strong> appear in the Google 3-pack for 73% more local search queries than businesses below that threshold. A 0.1-star increase in rating drives up to 25% more conversions. 74% of consumers only trust reviews written in the last 3 months — which means review <em>velocity</em>, not just total count, determines your local ranking over time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-policy">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Does this violate Google's review policies?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>No. PROOF Display is fully compliant with Google's review policies. The NFC tap opens the native Google review form directly — there is no incentivization, no filtering of reviews by sentiment, and no redirection away from Google. PROOF simply removes the friction from a voluntary action the customer was already willing to take.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-setup">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How long does setup take?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>Under 10 minutes. Plug in, connect to WiFi, enter your Google Business Profile URL, and PROOF starts pulling your live rating immediately. NFC is pre-configured. POS integration (Business Proof) adds another 5 minutes for Square or Shopify authorization.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-guarantee">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What does the 30-day money-back guarantee cover?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>If PROOF Display does not generate a measurable increase in your Google review velocity within 30 days of installation, return it for a full refund — no restocking fee, free return shipping. The guarantee covers the <strong>$499 hardware purchase</strong>. Software subscriptions (Business Proof at $25/month) are billed monthly and can be cancelled anytime with no penalty.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-low-rating">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What if my Google rating is low right now?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>That's exactly when PROOF helps most. <strong>Establish Mode</strong> shows your review trajectory — reviews added, rating climbing — rather than just a static number. A 3.8 becomes your starting line, not your ceiling. New reviews from genuinely happy customers push your rating up naturally. Portland merchants averaged a <strong>0.4-star rating increase</strong> (4.3 to 4.7) within 60 days. Establish Mode is included in the free Social Proof tier at no extra cost.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-pos-connect">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How does PROOF connect to my POS system?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>PROOF Business Proof tier ($25/month) integrates with <strong>Square and Shopify</strong>. Once connected, Screen 3 shows your real-time total orders and best-selling item, and Screen 4 lets you push daily promotions from your merchant dashboard. Authorization takes under 5 minutes — you connect your Square or Shopify account via OAuth in the PROOF merchant dashboard. No API keys, no developer required.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item" id="aeo-founding-merchant">
        <button class="faq-q" type="button" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What is the founding merchant program?</span>
          <span class="faq-chevron">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" hidden>
          <p>The founding merchant program is a limited pilot for <strong>10 locations in Portland, Oregon</strong>. Founding merchants receive priority onboarding, direct access to the PROOF team, and their feedback shapes the product before wider release. The hardware price is $499 with free shipping. The Social Proof tier is free forever. Business Proof is $25 per month — month-to-month, no annual contract required. Founding merchant pricing is locked for 12 months.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
{% schema %}
{
  "name": "PROOF FAQ",
  "tag": "div",
  "class": "proof-section",
  "settings": [
    { "type": "product", "id": "product", "label": "Checkout product" },
    { "type": "url", "id": "demo_video_url", "label": "Demo / video link" }
  ],
  "blocks": [{ "type": "@app" }],
  "presets": [{ "name": "PROOF FAQ" }]
}
{% endschema %}
